superMiscConds.notes: If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
Obtain and maintain full-time employment, attend school full-time or engage in combination of employment and school equal to full-time hours.

Pay costs of supervision and court obligations.  Participate in counseling, treatment and programs determined appropriate.  Follow through with recommendations.  Establish paternity if that has not been accomplished.  Comply with Family Court and child support orders.  Voting prohibited until sentence has been completed and civil rights are restored.

No use or possession of alcohol or controlled substances, except for those prescribed by treating health care provider.  Submit to random testing as required by agent.  Cooperate with AODA assessment and follow through with treatment, counseling and program recommendations, including aftercare programming.

Defendant Cedrick D Jones in court with attorney Carl Bradford Johnson.  Defendant Cedrick D Jones in custody.  Robert S. Repischak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Patricia Schaefer. TRANSCRIPT FILED 04-24-2015/tk
State provides stipulations to the Court, marked Ex #1, 2 & 3. The Court conducts a colloquy with the defendant regarding said stipulations.
Jury enters courtroom, Oath #2 given. Preliminary instructions given by the Court. Mr. Repischak gives opening statement for the State. Mr. Johnson gives opening statements for the Defense. 
The State reads stipulations of parties into the record. The State calls BQ - DSAT. Direct by the State. The State plays video marked Ex #4. Cross xam by defense. State calls Officer Garcia - DSAT. Direct by the State. State marks Ex #6-black handgun. State marks Ex #7-photo 1539 Packard; Ex #8-photo bicycle; Ex #9-photo of driveway deft ran up; Ex #10 & 11-photo of firearm; Ex #12-photo of cell phone. State marks Ex #4-DVD of surveillance video. State marks Ex #5-Cell phone. Cross xam by defense. Def marks Ex #13 Photo of driveway. Defense motions Ex 13 to be received. The State calls Officer Joshua LaForge - DSAT. Direct by the State. State moves Ex #7-12 into evidence. No cross xam by defense. Witness is excused and steps down. The State calls Officer Michael Seeger - DSAT. Direct by the State. Cross xam by defense. The witness is excused and steps down. The State has no further witnesses. The State moves Ex #1-12 into evidence. So received. The State rests.
Defense motions to dismiss.
BTC: motion to dismiss is denied.
Defense has no evidence/rebuttal. The defendant is declining to take the stand. The Court conducts colloquy with deft regarding his right to remain silent and his right to testify. BTC: The Court finds the defendant freely, knowingly and voluntarily waives his right to testify and wishes to remain silent.
PJI are reviewed.
Defense renews its motion to dismiss
BTC: motion to dismiss is denied
The State again rests. The Defense rests.
Mr. Repischak gives closing arguments for the State. Mr. Johnson gives closing arguments for the Defense.
The jury is instructed. Names tumbled, alternate chosen. Oath #4 given. Deliberations begin at 1:45 pm
The Court has received 2 requests from the jury. The jury requests to see the weapon. The State requests the weapon be checked to be sure it is unloaded - it was checked and is clear. The Court removed the bullets from the box. The box will be sent in. The jury wants all pictures. No objection by parties. The jury will recieve all pictures.

Defendant Cedrick D Jones in court with attorney Carl Bradford Johnson.  Defendant Cedrick D Jones in custody.  Robert S. Repischak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Patricia Schaefer. TRANSCRIPT FILED 04-24-2015/tk
Defense puts final offer as explained to deft on the record.  The defendant rejects the State's offer. The Court conducts a colloquy with the defendant regarding rejection of the State's offer. 

BTC: The defendant freely, knowingly and voluntarily rejects the State's offer and the matter will proceed to trial. 

Jury enters the courtroom at 2:22 pm. Oath #1 given. Voir dire by the Court. Voir dire by Mr. Repischak for the State. Voir dire by Mr. Johnson for the defense. Parties exercise their peremptory challenges. The jury is chosen.
No objection by the State. Defense makes a Batson challenge regarding the State's choice to strike #84. The State puts their reasons on the record. Defense objects to the State striking #84

BTC: The Court denies the Batson challenge.  Jury trial scheduled for September 17, 2014 at 08:45 am.

Defendant Cedrick D Jones in court with attorney Carl Bradford Johnson.  Defendant Cedrick D Jones in custody.  Robert S. Repischak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Patricia Schaefer. TRANSCRIPT FILED 04-24-2105/tk
Both the State and defense have filed bond motions. The State in 14CF588 to adj trial and defense regarding bond modification. The Defense objects to the State's request. 
The State indicates the issue is the firearm that was allegedly handled by the deft and tossed as he was running from police. Defense asked that the weapon be tested for fingerprints and DNA. Fingerprints were done but DNA was not due to the crime lab's reluctance to test the weapon. The State was able to convince the lab to test same, a swab was taken and it has been submitted to the crime lab. Defense isn't sure they actually asked that it be done but they did inquire. Defense objects to the adjournment citing the length of time deft has been in custody. Deft was granted a signature bond in 14CF588 so he is no longer being held on that matter. If the State's request is granted, Mr. Johnson asks to withdraw due to his limited ability to provide an adequate defense due to his new position.

Defense asks that bonds be modified from cash to just co-signature bonds with deft's mother with the GPS requirement in place. Although defense requested those bonds be converted to cash because deft was going to be held in custody, the deft's mother has not been able to post cash as requested and defense asks that bonds be converted to simply co-signature bonds. The State objects to the bond modification as requested citing the charges deft is now facing.

BTC: The Court believes the State's request for 'touch evidence' is not timely State's request is denied. Bond modification as requested by the defense is denied.
